<subSubSection id="E3FAC4FB1306FFF3FF7EFF78FD41FF1C" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFF78FD41FF1C" blockId="11.[163,1070,203,253]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: with worms, worm-shaped) refers to the shape of the internal structure of the aedeagus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3FAC4FB1306FFF3FF7EFEBFFDBDFB21" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" type="description">
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFEBFFD2BFEBA" blockId="11.[163,1070,268,347]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
Description: Small species; body length 
<quantity id="6C183A951306FFF3FD77FEBFFC9CFEC0" box="[682,807,268,290]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="6.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="7.3" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="6.8">6.8-7.8 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="6C183A951306FFF3FBDBFEBFFF48FEDF" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="3.05" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.9">2.9- 3.2 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FE7BFE9BFE43FEDF" box="[422,504,296,318]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body dark-brown with dark-reddish to reddish-brown elytra; legs and antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFEDAFC1AFE34" blockId="11.[163,1070,361,469]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
Head (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FF3BFEDAFE8BFE9E" box="[230,304,361,383]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad; punctation moderately coarse and moderately dense; interstices with fine, but distinct microreticulation. Eyes moderately small, approximately one third as long as postocular region in dorsal view, composed of approximately 40 defined ommatidia. Antenna approximately 
<quantity id="6C183A951306FFF3FCC7FE0CFCDCFE35" box="[794,871,447,469]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFE57FE50FDD3" blockId="11.[163,1070,483,562]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FEC5FE50FEDEFE18" box="[280,357,483,505]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) slender, 1.30-1.35 times as long as broad and indistinctly broader than head; punctation similar to that of head; impunctate midline relatively narrow; interstices without microreticulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFDF2FE52FD6E" blockId="11.[163,1070,577,655]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FF2EFDF2FEFAFDB6" box="[243,321,577,599]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) short, approximately 0.5 times as long as pronotum; punctation fine, shallow, and moderately dense. Hind wings completely reduced. Protarsomeres I-IV with pronounced sexual dimorphism.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFD2DFC33FD0C" blockId="11.[163,1070,670,749]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Abdomen 1.10-1.15 times as broad as elytra; punctation fine and very dense on tergites III-VI, somewhat sparser on tergites VII and VIII; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe; tergite VIII with weakly pronounced sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFD4FFD9AFBCF" blockId="11.[163,1071,763,1216]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
♂: tergite VIII with weakly convex posterior margin; sternites III-VI unmodified; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FED3FCABFEE5FCCF" box="[270,350,792,814]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse, with moderately extensive postero-median impression, this impression with numerous strongly modified stout black setae, posterior margin distinctly concave in the middle; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FD0DFCE2FCA1FC86" box="[720,794,849,871]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, with postero-median impression, posterior portion of impression with distinctly modified short and stout black setae, posterior excision relatively large, nearly V-shaped; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FF77FC15FEA7FC5D" box="[170,284,934,956]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Figs 32-33</figureCitation>
) rather large in relation to body size, 
<quantity id="6C183A951306FFF3FD6DFC15FCBBFC5D" box="[688,768,934,956]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
long and symmetric; ventral process of distinctive shape, relatively long, slender, and apically acute; dorsal plate with short and broad, flat, distinctly sclerotized, and apically weakly convex (dorsal view) apical portion, basal portion completely reduced, not noticeable; internal sac with curved internal structure of distinctive shape.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFB88FDBDFB21" blockId="11.[163,1071,763,1216]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<specimenCount id="BDE65CF91306FFF3FF7EFB88FF03FBB1" box="[163,184,1083,1104]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: posterior margin of tergite VIII obtusely angled in the middle; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FC06FB86FB9DFBAA" box="[987,1062,1077,1099]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="6C183A951306FFF3FF7EFBE0FF49FB89" box="[163,242,1107,1129]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
long, weakly oblong, posterior margin convexly produced; tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FC07FBE0FB9DFB88" box="[986,1062,1107,1129]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) with rather long and undivided antero-median portion, and with moderately long and slender postero-lateral processes; tergite X (
<figureCitation id="33DB8BF51306FFF3FDADFB3EFD06FB42" box="[624,701,1165,1187]" captionStart="Figs 28-35" captionStartId="10.[163,203,1433,1453]" captionTargetBox="[170,1057,197,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-84@10.[162,1069,197,1407]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 28-35: Lathrobium verminatum nov.sp.: (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30) male sternite VII; (31) male sternite VIII; (32-33) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (34) female sternite VIII; (35) female tergites IX and X. Scale bars: 28-29: 1.0 mm; 30-35: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412823/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) nearly flat, somewhat longer than antero-median portion of tergite X.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3FAC4FB1306FFF3FF7EFB63FE0EFA99" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFB63FE0EFA99" blockId="11.[163,1070,1232,1400]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
Comparative notes: The male sexual characters, particularly the derived morphology of the aedeagus (shapes of dorsal plate and of internal structure) do not suggest closer affiliations to any of the other described 
<taxonomicName id="6CE0ECF31306FFF3FCC2FAB9FC55FAC1" box="[799,1006,1290,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="99944B621306FFF3FCC2FAB9FC2DFAFE" box="[799,918,1290,1311]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Lathrobium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="692459921306FFF3FF7EFA9BFF43FADF" box="[163,248,1320,1342]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
. From the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="6CE0ECF31306FFF3FE02FA9BFDD9FADC" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[479,610,1320,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisuditum">
<emphasis id="99944B621306FFF3FE02FA9BFDD9FADC" box="[479,610,1320,1341]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. bisuditum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6CE0ECF31306FFF3FDAEFA9BFCB0FADC" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[627,779,1320,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verminatum">
<emphasis id="99944B621306FFF3FDAEFA9BFCB0FADC" box="[627,779,1320,1341]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. verminatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished by smaller body size, the greater number of ommatidia of the eyes, and by the completely different sexual characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3FAC4FB1306FFF3FF7EFA34FEEBFA39" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AB5F97701306FFF3FF7EFA34FEEBFA39" blockId="11.[163,1070,1415,1496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
Distribution and natural history Like 
<taxonomicName id="6CE0ECF31306FFF3FCADFA3BFC45FA7C" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[880,1022,1416,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisuditum">
<emphasis id="99944B621306FFF3FCADFA3BFC45FA7C" box="[880,1022,1416,1437]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. bisuditum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6CE0ECF31306FFF3FBC4FA3BFEA7FA5A" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verminatum">
<emphasis id="99944B621306FFF3FBC4FA3BFEA7FA5A" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. verminatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably endemic to the Xiling Xue Shan, where the specimens were sifted from litter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
